# Portfolio Engine Rules

## Average Cost Basis (ACB) — Must Preserve

`calculate_holdings()` walks transactions in date order. Do not refactor this
into a groupby or vectorised operation — the chronological order is load-bearing.

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — sell reduces cost proportionally using running avg_cost
avg_cost = lots[ticker]["total_cost"] / current_qty
realised_pnl += (sell_price - avg_cost) * qty_sold
lots[ticker]["total_cost"] -= avg_cost * qty_sold

# ❌ WRONG — recalculating avg from raw data ignores prior sells
avg_cost = investment_df[investment_df["ticker"] == t]["amount"].sum() / total_qty
```

## Price Caching — Must Preserve

All yfinance calls go through `get_live_prices()`. Never call `yf.Ticker()` directly
from any other method. The 15-minute TTL is enforced by `_is_cache_fresh()`.

```python
# ✅ CORRECT
prices = self.get_live_prices(tickers)

# ❌ WRONG — bypasses cache
price = yf.Ticker(ticker).fast_info.last_price
```

Use attribute access on `fast_info`, not dictionary access:
```python
# ✅  fast_info.last_price
# ❌  fast_info["last_price"]   ← broken in yfinance 1.2+
```

## Portfolio Metrics

`compute_portfolio_metrics()` must always return these five columns:
`total_capital_invested`, `total_market_value`, `total_unrealised_pnl`,
`total_realised_pnl`, `total_dividends`. Do not remove or rename them —
`add_snapshot()` and the snapshot header depend on this schema.

## Validation

`run_validations()` must be called at the end of every `run_pipeline()` call.
All four checks must pass before the result is returned to the caller.
